"The recent adverse weather has prompted many businesses to look again at the impact that loss or damage to property could cause. In some cases, regulation dictates that financial documents and other industry-specific records must be stored for a set length of time. If they are destroyed, an organisation could be in breach of regulatory compliance and may be unable to help customers or easily obtain replacement files. As such, organisations that rely on paper-based processes and records could risk damage to customer service in the event of loss due to fire, flood or any other unexpected event."
